OL,3,CThe soaring numbers of families
OL,4,Cstruggling to care for a loved one
OL,5,Cwith dementia
OL,7,FMore than 700,000 people are looking
OL,8,Fafter a relative with dementia. Many
OL,9,Fof those feel they have no where to
OL,10,Fturn when their loved one puts
OL,11,Fthemselves or others at risk of harm.
OL,12,FDementia can affect a person's ability
OL,13,Fto manage their reactions to difficult
OL,14,Fthoughts and feelings. This can lead
OL,15,Fto them experiencing such intense
OL,16,Fstates of distress that they become
OL,17,Fverbally or physically aggressive.
